description:
A bizarre accident at school lands Sonia in hot water after she bumps into Flora, who is finding herself at the lowest point in life. Will the two be able to come to terms? Or is the friendship they once knew gone for good...?
https://www.patreon.com/Tamers12345

comments.text:
Based on the flag that we see in the establishing shot of their middle school, we can narrow down where the Sonic Underground lives in the US to: Idaho, Kansas, Kentucky, Maine, Michigan, Minnesota, Nebraska, New Hampshire, New York, Pennsylvania, Utah, Vermont, and Wisconsin.

The climate leads me to believe that this is either midwestern or northeastern United States, and previous episodes have established that the Sonic household is within driving distance of Canada (Despite Sonic's adopted parents driving a poor person car.)

Ultimately I think the location can be narrowed down to Maine, Michigan, Minnesota, New Hampshire, Upstate New York, or Vermont. Assuming it's also a short drive to Canada's largest concentration of maple trees in eastern Quebec, where a maple syrup farm would likely be, Vermont, New Hampshire, Upstate New York and Maine are the most likely candidates.

TL;DR version: The Sonic Underground most likely lives in the New England region or Upstate New York, specifically Maine, Vermont, New Hampshire, NY.
